Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer will be visiting Colombia on July 21-22. He will have official meetings with President Ivan Duque, President-Elect Gustavo Petro, and Vice President-Elect Francia Marquez. Accompanying him will be National Security Advisor to the Vice President Phil Gordon, Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs Brian Nichols, and National Security Council Senior Director for the Western Hemisphere Juan Gonzalez. The purpose of the visit is to discuss various topics including combatting climate change, supporting peace implementation and rural development, reducing violence and combating criminal groups, promoting equitable and sustainable economic growth, and addressing other regional and global issues.